        "content": "<p>myunbin opened <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13786\">PR #13786</a> from <code>myunbin:remove-redundants</code> to <code>bytecodealliance:main</code>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>This PR removes a redundant simplification rule that is already covered by constant canonicalization in <code>cprop.isle</code>.</p>\n<p>The rule <code>(2^n) * x --&gt; x &lt;&lt; n</code> is redundant because it can be derived by first canonicalizing the constant operand:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"o\">^</span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"o\">^</span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&lt;&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>So only <code>x * (2^n) --&gt; (x &lt;&lt; n)</code> rule is needed.</p>\n</blockquote>",
